{{- define "anomaly-logging" -}}
{{- if eq .RoleType "reviewer"}}

ANOMALY LOGGING:
| Observation | Type | Required Fields |
|-------------|------|-----------------|
| Coder retry loop visible | retry_loop | count, error_pattern |
| Implementation differs from spec | scope_deviation | — |
| Workaround taken | workaround | — |
| Technical debt introduced | debt_created | — |
| Spec assumption contradicted | assumption_violated | assumption, reality |
| Spec changed since task creation | spec_changed | — |
| Own review stuck in command loop | reviewer_loop | count, command_pattern |
Format: anomalies: [{id, type, task, reporter, timestamp (ISO 8601), details: {<fields>}}]
{{- else if eq .RoleType "orchestrator"}}

ANOMALY LOGGING:
| Event | Type | Required Fields |
|-------|------|-----------------|
| Two coders failed same task | hypothesis_exhaustion | — |
| Spec gap discovered | spec_gap | — |
| Review stuck in cycles | review_deadlock | — |
| Multiple reviewers failed | review_exhaustion | reviewers_failed, common_blocker |
| Protocol ambiguity | system_ambiguity | protocol_section, question |
Format: anomalies: [{id, type, task, reporter, timestamp (ISO 8601), details: {<fields>}}]
{{- else}}

ANOMALY LOGGING:
| Event | Type | Required Fields |
|-------|------|-----------------|
| >2 iterations on same error | retry_loop | count, error_pattern |
| Accepting suboptimal solution | trade_off | what, why, debt_created |
| Spec doesn't cover case | spec_ambiguity | — |
| External service blocking | external_blocker | blocker_service |
| Spec assumption proven false | assumption_violated | assumption, reality |
Format: anomalies: [{id, type, task, reporter, timestamp (ISO 8601), details: {<fields>}}]
{{- end}}
{{- end -}}
